How to include EzioMobile.framework in a Xcode project
======================================================

1- In the project navigator, select your project
2- Select your target
3- Select the 'Build Phases' tab
4- Open 'Link Binaries With Libraries' expander
5- Click the '+' button
6- Select your EzioMobile.framework
7- (optional) Drag and drop the added framework to the 'Frameworks' group

Others dependencies required
============================

Add the Security.framework into your project
----------------------------------------------

1- In the project navigator, select your project
2- Select your target
3- Select the 'Build Phases' tab
4- Open 'Link Binaries With Libraries' expander
5- Click the '+' button
6- Select your Security.framework
7- (optional) Drag and drop the added framework to the 'Frameworks' group

Add the SystemConfiguration.framework into your project
----------------------------------------------

1- In the project navigator, select your project
2- Select your target
3- Select the 'Build Phases' tab
4- Open 'Link Binaries With Libraries' expander
5- Click the '+' button
6- Select your SystemConfiguration.framework
7- (optional) Drag and drop the added framework to the 'Frameworks' group


Add the libsqlite3.0.dylib into your poject
----------------------------------------

1- In the project navigator, select your project
2- Select your target
3- Select the 'Build Phases' tab
4- Open 'Link Binaries With Libraries' expander
5- Click the '+' button
6- Select your libsqlite3.0.dylib
7- (optional) Drag and drop the added framework to the 'Frameworks' group

Add the libc++.dylib into your poject
----------------------------------------

1- In the project navigator, select your project
2- Select your target
3- Select the 'Build Phases' tab
4- Open 'Link Binaries With Libraries' expander
5- Click the '+' button
6- Select your libc++.dylib
7- (optional) Drag and drop the added framework to the 'Frameworks' group


Add the -ObjC compilation option in the "Other Linker Flags"
------------------------------------------------------------

1- In the project navigator, select your project
2- Select your target
3- Select the 'Build Settings' tab
4- Open 'Linking' group
5- In the "Other Linker Flags" item add -ObjC

If DEBUG version of the framework is used
============================

Enable "Enable Code Coverage Support" and "Instrument Program Flow"
------------------------------------------------------------
1- In the project navigator, select your project
2- Select your target
3- Select the 'Build Settings' tab
4- Open 'Code generation' group
5- In "Enable Code Coverage Support" set to YES
6- In "Instrument Program Flow" set to YES



